				caption: '',
				content: "‘Great ruth came upon the men of Israel’; this is certainly the sense of the Septuagint Greek, and perhaps of the Latin. But the Hebrew text appears to say that anger was roused against Israel: and the term used generally refers to divine anger. It seems not impossible that some words of the original story have dropped out."
